abstract: Ms. Carroll says that President Trump assaulted her in the 1990s, and that she has the dress she was wearing during the incident.
snippet: Ms. Carroll says that President Trump assaulted her in the 1990s, and that she has the dress she was wearing during the incident.
lead_paragraph: The writer E. Jean Carroll, who has accused Donald J. Trump of raping her in the 1990s and is suing him for defamation, asked on Thursday that he provide a DNA sample to determine whether his genetic material is on a dress she says she had on at the time of the incident.

abstract: Senator Marsha Blackburn Alan M. Dershowitz, who argued an expansive view of presidential power.
snippet: Senator Marsha Blackburn Alan M. Dershowitz, who argued an expansive view of presidential power.
lead_paragraph: Senator Marsha Blackburn, Republican of Tennessee, on Thursday defended the president’s lawyer, Alan M. Dershowitz, who faced an onslaught of criticism after making this argument on Wednesday: “If the president does something that he thinks will help him get elected, in the public interest, that cannot be the kind of quid pro quo that results in impeachment.”

abstract: The Perla family of El Salvador has slipped into a daily rhythm in Mexico while they wait for the U.S. to decide whether to grant them asylum.
snippet: The Perla family of El Salvador has slipped into a daily rhythm in Mexico while they wait for the U.S. to decide whether to grant them asylum.
lead_paragraph: TIJUANA, Mexico — The Perla family of El Salvador has slipped into a daily rhythm in Mexico while they wait for the U.S. to decide whether to grant them asylum.
headline_main: US Finds Ally in Mexico as Asylum Policy Marks First Year
headline_print_headline: US Finds Ally in Mexico as Asylum Policy Marks First Year

abstract: Senator Rand Paul of Kentucky has said he wants to ask about the origins of the impeachment inquiry, but Chief Justice Roberts refused.
snippet: Senator Rand Paul of Kentucky has said he wants to ask about the origins of the impeachment inquiry, but Chief Justice Roberts refused.
lead_paragraph: Chief Justice John G. Roberts refused on Thursday to read aloud a question submitted by Senator Rand Paul of Kentucky that would have named a person widely believed to be the C.I.A. whistle-blower in the Ukraine affair.

abstract: As the Senate lurched toward a vote to acquit President Donald Trump on impeachment charges, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo played clean-up in the country at the center of the inquiry on Friday.
snippet: As the Senate lurched toward a vote to acquit President Donald Trump on impeachment charges, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo played clean-up in the country at the center of the inquiry on Friday.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — As the Senate lurched toward a vote to acquit President Donald Trump on impeachment charges, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo played clean-up in the country at the center of the inquiry on Friday.
headline_main: Pompeo Plays Clean-Up in Ukraine as Trump Trial Nears End
headline_print_headline: Pompeo Plays Clean-Up in Ukraine as Trump Trial Nears End

abstract: Refocusing a debate on war and peace in the midst of the Senate impeachment trial, the Democratic-controlled House on Thursday approved measures reasserting congressional authority over war powers.
snippet: Refocusing a debate on war and peace in the midst of the Senate impeachment trial, the Democratic-controlled House on Thursday approved measures reasserting congressional authority over war powers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Refocusing a debate on war and peace in the midst of the Senate impeachment trial, the Democratic-controlled House on Thursday approved measures reasserting congressional authority over war powers.
headline_main: House Backs Measures Asserting Congressional War Powers
headline_print_headline: House Backs Measures Asserting Congressional War Powers

abstract: Mr. Biden’s attack on his rival in Iowa came hours after another leading candidate, Pete Buttigieg, criticized both men, in a day of sparring that underscored the pressure they all face to excel in Monday’s caucuses.
snippet: Mr. Biden’s attack on his rival in Iowa came hours after another leading candidate, Pete Buttigieg, criticized both men, in a day of sparring that underscored the pressure they all face to excel in Monday’s caucuses.
lead_paragraph: PELLA, Iowa — In one of his most direct confrontations yet with his top rival in the Iowa caucuses, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Thursday called out Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont for not being a Democrat even as Mr. Sanders makes a competitive run for that party’s presidential nomination, and Mr. Biden also jabbed Mr. Sanders’s record on gun control in among his most detailed remarks on the matter to date.

abstract: The law has been used to justify all manner of military strikes since Congress approved it to authorize President George W. Bush to take military action in Iraq.
snippet: The law has been used to justify all manner of military strikes since Congress approved it to authorize President George W. Bush to take military action in Iraq.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House on Thursday moved to block President Trump from taking military action against Iran without the approval of Congress, voting to repeal a 2002 war authorization and to bar him from using federal funds to mount an unauthorized strike against Tehran.
